message: I'm so happy I finally we got something that can be shown in the hackathon.

It seems like you are feeling more positive about the project that you are working on with the team. The hackathon is a great opportunity to showcase your hard work and creativity, and it's great that you have something to show already. 

Is there anything else you would like to discuss?
It sucks I don't have more time to do my homeork..

It sounds like you might be feeling stressed or anxious about the time you have to complete your homework. It's normal to have these feelings sometimes, but remember that you can always reach out for support to manage these feelings, and that you can also take steps to manage your time in a way that feels less overwhelming. 

Do you want to explore some options for managing these feelings?
I'm kind of sad that I won't be able to return home and see my parents again..

I understand how that can be challenging, it can be difficult to cope with the uncertainty of when you may be able to see your parents again. 

It is important to acknowledge these feelings of sadness and to allow yourself to feel these emotions. However, it is also important to remember that you can find other ways to stay connected to your parents in the meantime. 

What do you think would help you feel more connected to your parents while you are away from home?
